      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(qa-lab): add live turn timeout env override",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nQA Lab live-frontier runs sometimes need a longer per-turn timeout than the built-in model-family floors allow, especially when validating slow frontier/provider routes or shared-runner conditions. Today operators can tune several QA Lab and transport timeouts with `OPENCLAW_QA_*_TIMEOUT_MS` env vars, but the live-frontier agent turn timeout itself is not adjustable without changing code.\n\nThis is intentionally separate from #96567. That PR fixes the `claude-cli/*` timeout bucket classification. This PR adds the operator escape hatch for slow live-frontier runs.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nThe existing `resolveQaLiveTurnTimeoutMs` path already receives a caller fallback and then lets the provider policy enforce model-specific floors. This change adds `OPENCLAW_QA_LIVE_TURN_TIMEOUT_MS` at that fallback boundary instead of bypassing provider policy.\n\nThat means:\n\n- A higher env value raises the floor for live-frontier turns.\n- A lower env value does not accidentally undercut existing provider-specific floors like GPT-5 or Claude Opus.\n- Invalid env values fall back to the existing timeout behavior.\n\n## User Impact\n\nQA Lab operators can run slow live-frontier scenarios with:\n\n```bash\nOPENCLAW_QA_LIVE_TURN_TIMEOUT_MS=420000 pnpm openclaw qa suite --provider-mode live-frontier ...\n```\n\nExisting runs without the env var are unchanged. Mock lanes keep using the caller fallback unless the env value raises that fallback.\n\n## Evidence\n\nTest Plan (run from repo root):\n\n- `pnpm test extensions/qa-lab/src/live-timeout.test.ts` - PASS, 1 file / 8 tests.\n- `pnpm tsgo:extensions` - PASS.\n- `pnpm format:docs:check docs/help/testing.md` - PASS, docs formatting clean.\n- `git diff --check` - PASS.\n- `~/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/openclaw-pre-pr.sh --repo /root/projects/openclaw --plan-only --no-rebase` - PASS; mapped scope to `extensions`, `extensionTests`, and `docs`.\n- `pnpm tsgo:extensions:test` - PASS.\n\nKnown local tooling gap:\n\n- `node scripts/run-oxlint.mjs --tsconfig config/tsconfig/oxlint.extensions.json extensions/qa-lab/src/live-timeout.test.ts extensions/qa-lab/src/live-timeout.ts` was attempted twice, but the local wrapper stayed in `prepare-extension-package-boundary-artifacts.mjs` with no lint diagnostics; the attempts were stopped so no local check process remained. CI remains the canonical oxlint proof for this lane.\n\n🤖 AI-assisted with GPT-5 Codex.\n",
